(34, 's2QS7O5tTs0', 'paper_supplementary', 'raw', 'raw', 'no_voice', '10.1016/j.cviu.2013.12.006', '10.1016/j.cviu.2013.12.006', 'Head pose estimation from monocular sequences', 'In order to estimate the Point of Interest (POI) that the user is looking at while performing a pointing gesture in a non-intrusive way, we employ a technique that tracks the orientation of the users head with high accuracy using a monocular setup. This is achieved by tracking off-plane facial rotations in horizontal direction around the heads y-axis via a feature-based face tracking approach based on Least-Squares Matching (LSM). The algorithm is able to maintain significant success rates (more than 50%) even for angles up to 120, where only a small part of the facial patch is visible. \n\nReferences:\nPateraki M., Baltzakis H., Trahanias P., 2014. Visual estimation of pointed targets for robot guidance via fusion of face pose and hand orientation.  Computer Vision and Image Understanding. \nDoi: http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.cviu.2013.12.006', '2015-03-02 12:57:27', 'head pose estimation, Monocular, least squares', NULL, NULL, 'FORTH Vision and Robotics', 'UCRhRvEG7DJJ7f2B1kMKkgGg', 54, 226, 1, 0, 1, 0, 0, '2020-07-21 18:40:52'),
