(77, '8N-tkrxAEWw', 'paper_reference', 'creative', 'presentation', 'narrative', '10.1016/j.chb.2013.07.014', 'sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0747563213002525', 'Thunderf00t - Busted', 'Time to drop some L0G1C on Thunderf00t!\n\nRegarding my comments about MRAs:\nAlthough I do not endorse the MRA position, I do not believe all MRAs are equal and I will always listen to their point of view and not dismiss them simply because of the label they attach to (just like I hope they listen to me even if I identify as a Feminist). I understand that working together wouldn\'t work in practice, my point is that one movement doesn\'t invalidate the other. MRAs and feminists both believe there are issues that affect one gender more than the other, and I don\'t mind if MRAs want to fight for men\'s rights, so long as that fight isn\'t a fight against Feminism.\n\nArticles:\n=======\n\nWe Might Be Witnessing The \'Death of An Identity\'\nhttp://kotaku.com/we-might-be-witnessing-the-death-of-an-identity-1628203079\n\nThe End of Gamers\nhttp://dangolding.tumblr.com/post/95985875943/the-end-of-gamers\n\n\'Gamers\' don\'t have to be your audience. \'Gamers\' are over.\nhttp://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/224400/Gamers_dont_have_to_be_your_audience_Gamers_are_over.php\n\nAnita\'s Irony: Every Hater Proves Anita Sarkeesian Right\nhttp://blogs.houstonpress.com/artattack/2014/08/anitas_irony.php\n\nStop ruining my escapist fantasies, Sarkeesian haters\nhttp://www.theverge.com/2014/8/28/6078517/stop-ruining-my-escapist-fantasies-sarkeesian-haters\n\nThe death of the gamers and the women who killed them\nhttp://arstechnica.com/gaming/2014/08/the-death-of-the-gamers-and-the-women-who-killed-them/\n\nThe Problem With \'The Casual Cruelty\' Against Women in Video Games\nhttp://kotaku.com/the-problem-with-the-casual-cruelty-against-women-in-vi-1626659439\n\nAvengers Director Offers Support to Feminist Frequency Creator After Death Threats\nhttp://www.gamespot.com/articles/avengers-director