(102, 'IflW_oaOJqg', 'paper_explanation', 'presentation', 'presentation', 'dialogue', '10.1371/journal.pcbi.1003588', '10.1371/journal.pcbi.1003588', 'IIT 3.0 Tutorial | Tsuchiya Lab', 'This is a recording of an online tutorial giving an overview of Integrated Information Theory of Consciousness 3.0. (Oizumi et al., 2014, PLoS comp biol, https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1003588) Its application to fly LFPs data mentioned in the video is reported in Leung et al, 2020, bioRxiv (https://doi.org/10.1101/2020.05.17.090001). \n\nYou may be interested in other IIT talks.\n"What is visible across the visual field? (and what is the visual field, anyways?)" by Dr. Andrew Haun (https://youtu.be/pG6dyLAJjRo)\n\nPresentation title - IIT 3.0 Tutorial\nSpeaker - Dr. Ariel Zeleznikow-Johnston, Mr. Angus Leung, Mr. Yota Kawashima, and A/Prof. Naotsugu Tsuchiya from Tsuchiya lab in Monash University\n\nThis tutorial will give an overview of the theory - from its starting point in phenomenological analysis of consciousness through to its quantification of consciousness by Integrated Information. Our main resource will be the supplementary slides \'Calculating Phi\' (https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1006343.s001) from Mayner et al., 2018, PLoS comp biol (https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pcbi.1006343).', '2020-05-09 02:43:21', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Monash Consciousness Group', 'UCvRuQWqbKbHJFCC4xabOI4g', 6355, 849, 28, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-24 10:00:01'),
