(126, '6FXbvPHTCtM', 'paper_reference', 'presentation', 'none', 'narrative', '10.1007/s10710-013-9210-0', '10.1007/s10710-013-9210-0', '[TLIT]: Deep learning for object detection and recognition', 'Thang Long Information Technology Club\nPhd. Nguyn Quang Uy\nTitle: Deep learning for object detection and recognition\n\n\nPresenter: Dr. Nguyen Quang Uy\n\n\nAffiliation: Faculty of IT, Le Quy Don Technical University\n\n\nAbstract: In this seminar we will present a tutorial about deep learning, the best machine learning technique developed in recent years. Particularly, we will introduce in detailed Convolutional Neural Network, the most popular deep learning structure and the application of this deep network to object detection and recognition.\n\n\nMachine learning is the method that allows computers to solve problems by themself. Recently, deep learning has emerged as the best machine learning technique. Deep learning has a profound impact to industry that makes many major IT corporations like Google, Microsoft, Apple and Facebook creating their own research groups and building many impressive applications (face tagging in Facebook, Language Translation in Google, siri speech recognition in Iphone, etc.).\n\n\nAbout the presenter:\n\nDr. Nguyen Quang Uy received his PhD degree from University College Dublin, Ireland in 2011. Currently, the senior lecturer at Le Quy Don Technical University. Dr. Nguyen is widely recognized as one of the main contributors to the development of semantic method in Genetic Programming (*). He is author and co-author of about 40 publications in Genetic Programming, machine learning and related areas (**). He research interest includes Machine learning, Evolutionary Algorithms and Genetic Programming.\n\n\n(*): Vanneschi et al. A survey of semantic methods in genetic programming, Genetic Programming and Evolvable Machines, 2014,\n\nhttp://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10710-013-9210-0\n\n\n(**): https://scholar.google.com.vn/citations