(138, 'fouSmgZBXsU', 'paper_reference', 'creative', 'none', 'narrative', '10.1016/j.chb.2014.03.003', 'sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0747563214001241', 'How Social Media Is Destroying Our Brains', 'Social media is addicting - practically all of us have dealt with this. Are instagram and facebook on your side? No, they are built to profit off of your need for connection, while they truly have a very negative effect on our psychology.\n\nWays Social Media Ruins Everything\nhttps://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/feeling-it/201603/3-ways-social-media-ruins-everything\n\nSocial Media Affects Our Brains\nhttps://www.forbes.com/sites/alicegwalton/2017/06/30/a-run-down-of-social-medias-effects-on-our-mental-health/#75e6fa492e5a\n\nFacebook Predicts Decline in Subjective Well-Being\nhttps://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0069841&mbid=synd_msnhealth\n\nSocial Media Use and Social Isolation \nhttps://www.ajpmonline.org/article/S0749-3797(17)30016-8/fulltext\n\nWhy Social Media Makes Us Bitter\nhttps://www.forbes.com/sites/alicegwalton/2013/01/22/jealous-of-your-facebook-friends-why-social-media-makes-us-bitter/#6fc23e4e35cc\n\nFacebooks Emotional Consequences\nhttps://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0747563214001241\n\nMusic from Bensound.com\n\nThanks to Tristan Reed (writing), Troy W. Hudson (VO) for helping to create this video!', '2020-01-15 22:00:05', 'social media, social media addiction, social media ruins everything, social media marketing, instagram, facebook, psychology', NULL, NULL, 'TopThink', 'UCMlGmHokrQRp-RaNO7aq4Uw', 653, 94884, 3693, 69, 357, 0, 0, '2020-07-25 14:05:43'),
