(164, 'G6L7TzLhH7Y', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1038/nclimate2392', '10.1038/nclimate2392', 'Lifestyle changes in pathways compatible with climate change mitigation goals and development goals', 'This is a talk prepared for ICTA-UAB International Virtual Conference  Towards low-carbon lifestyles  on 6 May 2020. https://lifestyle-changes.org/ \n\n\nIt gives three focuses on the role of lifestyle changes in mitigation pathways, one from the IPCC assessment reports, one from the modelling of lifestyle changes perspective, and one exploring public policies issues from the example of the French Low-Carbon Strategy.\n\nBy Cline Guivarch, Associate Professor at Ecole des Ponts, Senior researcher at CIRED. http://www2.centre-cired.fr/GUIVARCH-Celine\nTwitter : @CelineGuivarch\n\nDisclaimer : The opinions I will express are mine, and do not necessarily reflect the positions from the three institutions mentionned.\n\nLinks and references mentioned in the talk:\n\nIPCC AR5 WGIII chapter 6 (2014) https://www.ipcc.ch/report/ar5/wg3/\n\nFuss, Sabine, Josep G. Canadell, Glen P. Peters, Massimo Tavoni, Robbie M. Andrew, Philippe Ciais, Robert B. Jackson, Chris D. Jones, Florian Kraxner, Nebosja Nakicenovic. 2014.  Betting on negative emissions . Nature Climate Change 4 (10): 850 53. https://doi.org/10.1038/nclimate2392 \n\n\n\nSmith, Pete, Steven J. Davis, Felix Creutzig, Sabine Fuss, Jan Minx, Benoit Gabrielle, Etsushi Kato, Robert B. Jackson, Annette Cowie, Elmar Kriegler. 2016.  Biophysical and economic limits to negative CO2 emissions . Nature Climate Change 6 (1): 42 50. https://doi.org/10.1038/nclimate2870 \n\n\nvan Vuuren, Detlef P., Andries F. Hof, Marisse A. E. van Sluisveld, Keywan Riahi. 2017.  Open Discussion of Negative Emissions Is Urgently Needed . Nature Energy 2 (12): 902. https://doi.org/10.1038/s41560-017-0055-2.\n\nHeck, Vera, Dieter Gerten, Wolfgang Lucht, Alexander Popp. 2018.  Biomass-Based Negative Emissions Difficult to Reconcile with Planetary Boundaries 