(192, 'w638PpSwvy0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pbio.1001825', '10.1371/journal.pbio.1001825', 'The world of animal cloning', 'This video outlines the process and mechanisms used for cloning animals. This topic has gotten more exposure with a greater number of individuals interested in cloning their pets, as well as research into the implications of cloning cells. The video addresses the history of animal cloning, the overall process of cloning, and the various applications that cloning can have in the future. The video focuses on the use of cloning as a method for preventing extinctions and also beneficial health implications that cloning may have.\n\nThis video was made by the McMaster Demystifying Medicine students Pouriya Sadeghi, Jonah Standard, Rachel Aubrey and Vaishna Kumaran.\n\nCopyright McMaster University 2019\n\nReferences: \n\nKeefer, C. L. (2015). Artificial cloning of domestic animals. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 112(29), 88748878. https://doi.org/10.1073/pnas.1501718112\n\nIbtisham, F., Fahd Qadir, M. M., Xiao, M., & An, L. (2017). Animal cloning applications and issues. Russian Journal of Genetics, 53(9), 965971. https://doi.org/10.1134/S102279541709006X\n\nSinclair, K. D., Corr, S. A., Gutierrez, C. G., Fisher, P. A., Lee, J.-H., Rathbone, A. J.,  Gardner, D. S. (2016). Healthy ageing of cloned sheep. Nature Communications, 7(1), 12359. https://doi.org/10.1038/ncomms12359\n\nNovak, B. (2018). De-Extinction. Genes, 9(11), 548. https://doi.org/10.3390/genes9110548\n\nFriese, C., & Marris, C. (2014). Making De-Extinction Mundane? PLoS Biology, 12(3), e1001825. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.1001825\n\nRichmond, D. J., Sinding, M. S., & Gilbert, M. T. P. (2016). The potential and pitfalls of deextinction. Zoologica Scripta, 45(S1), 2236. https://doi.org/10.1111/zsc.12212\n\nChoi, S. (2004). Cloning human stem cells. Canadian Medical Association Journal, 170(7), 10901090. https://doi.org/10.1503/cmaj.1040424', '2019-10-28 22:58:10', 'McMaster University, Demystifying Medicine, Cloning, Extinction, Animals, Cells, pets, cloning cells', NULL, 'en', 'Demystifying Medicine', 'UCEwEYnO7yey-oBzyNu-AauQ', 367, 2365, 21, 2, 5, 0, 0, '2020-07-28 10:38:54'),
(193, 'BkhoA2dq9jA', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224', '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224, journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224', 'Physical Profiles Using DNA', 'Companies can now recreate physical profiles from peoples DNA. Is this going to be the future of how we catch criminals? In this video we talk about the technology behind DNA phenotyping, what it is capable of doing and how this could affect criminal cases in court. \n\n SOCIAL MEDIA // \n// Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/steministas/\n// Facebook: https://facebook.com/steministas\n// Twitter: https://twitter.com/steministasunc\n MUSIC // Song: Ikson - Ocean (Vlog No Copyright Music) Music promoted by Vlog No Copyright Music. Video Link: https://youtu.be/BzSv-tRyhac\n FTC // This video is sponsored by the National Science Foundation https://www.nsf.gov/.  \n\n SOURCES //\nhttp://blogs.discovermagazine.com/d-brief/2015/02/25/dna-image-face/#.W23XRdgzqRt\nhttps://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/24/science/building-face-and-a-case-on-dna.html\nhttps://www.smithsonianmag.com/innovation/how-accurately-can-scientists-reconstruct-persons-face-from-dna-180968951/\nhttps://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/19/nyregion/dna-phenotyping-new-york-police.html\nhttp://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224', '2018-10-23 13:56:11', 'DNA, physical profile, golden state killer, genetics, criminal, genotyping, paragon nanolabs', NULL, NULL, 'Steministas', 'UC2ffHN_L2J-g-9_K99OUUmw', 709, 48, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-28 10:38:54'),
(194, 'lKyK1mprGkQ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224', '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224', 'Criminals Beware: Faces Recreated With ONLY DNA - The Future This Week', 'Penn State scientists and an image specialist out of Belguim  have managed to create highly accurate "mugshots" of individuals using only DNA.\n\nStories:\nhttp://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22129613.600-genetic-mugshot-recreates-faces-from-nothing-but-dna.html?full=true#.U0bO8_ldXTr\n\nhttp://www.plosgenetics.org/article/info:doi/10.1371/journal.pgen.1004224\n\nImages:\n\nBackground\nhttp://hateplow.tumblr.com/post/39753846284\n\nBill Gates Mugshot\nhttp://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Bill_Gates_mugshot.png\n\nDNA\nhttp://ian.umces.edu/imagelibrary/albums/userpics/12789/normal_ian-symbol-dna-sequencing-gel.png\n\n\nMusic:\n\nNo Future by Bannau\nhttps://soundcloud.com/futurex-news/sets/the-future-this-week-playlist', '2014-04-10 20:10:13', 'futurex, the future this week, science, technology, culture, human, breakthroughs, social, DNA mugshot, dna study, face made with dna, 3d faces, Pennsylvania State University (College/University), european, african, ancestry, criminal DNA, face shape, DNA, DNA (Award-Winning Work), College (TV Genre), 3d images, hard science, human face, with dna, face made from dna, 23 and ME, 23andme, New Scientist', NULL, NULL, 'FutureX News', 'UCpfaKA-jIV3BQq-wP3fvkAw', 202, 234, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-28 10:38:54'),
(195, 'NHREZ80pcgE', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1038/ngeo2075', '10.1038/ngeo2075', 'Idade da Terra 3: Datao Absoluta', 'Idade da Terra - terceiro vdeo. Neste falo efetivamente como a idade da Terra  calculada, como depende do mineral zirco e da meia vida do urnio 238.\n\n\n\n\nPara saber mais sobre o tema do vdeo:\n\nhttps://www.nature.com/articles/35051550\nCosmos: A Spacetime Odyssey  Ep. 7\n\nhttp://www.sciencemag.org/news/2017/08/record-shattering-27-million-year-old-ice-core-reveals-start-ice-ages\n\nhttp://science.sciencemag.org/content/310/5756/1914.full?sid=ddb3c2a4-9b7d-4eaa-a28b-b8328cb580f5\n\nHow Old Is Planet Earth\nhttp://science.sciencemag.org/content/300/5625/1513\n\n\nJack Hills Zircon: Scientists Discover Oldest-Known Fragment of Earth\nhttp://www.sci-news.com/geology/science-jack-hills-zircon-oldest-known-fragment-earth-01779.html\n\nValley JW et al. Hadean age for a post-magma-ocean zircon confirmed by atom-probe tomography. Nature Geoscience, published online February 23, 2014; doi: 10.1038/ngeo2075\n\nAcasta Gneiss\nhttps://link.springer.com/referenceworkentry/10.1007%2F978-3-642-11274-4_11\n\nO\'Neil, J., Carlson, R. W., Francis, D., & Stevenson, R. K. (2008). Neodymium-142 evidence for Hadean mafic crust. Science, 321(5897), 1828-1831.\nhttp://courses.washington.edu/bangblue/ONeil-Oldest_Rock_4.28Ga-Sci08.pdf\n\nGEOCRONOLOGIA - CANAL SUR\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=khNTHCrJ8VE\nLaboratrio de Geocronologia\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_LxrQAJJeAI\n\nGeocronologia: O tempo registrado nas rochas\nhttp://www.igc.usp.br/index.php?id=304\n\n\n\nImagens e vdeos:\n\nLunar Olivine Basalt 15555 sample collected from the moon by the Apollo 15 mission, at station 9A on the rim of Hadley Rille. It was formed around 3.3 billion years ago. On display in the National Museum of Natural History.\nhttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Lunar_Olivine_Basalt_15555_from_Apollo_15_in_National_Museum_of_Natural_History.jpg\n\nMeteorito de Hoba\nhttps://pixabay.com/pt/meteorito-stone-hoba-nam%C3%ADbia-700836/\n\nhttps://pixabay.com/pt/meteorito-stone-rock-91891/\n\nSand-sized grains of zircon\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zircon#/media/File:ZirconUSGOV.jpg\n\nRob Lavinsky, iRocks.com  CC-BY-SA-3.0 [CC BY-SA 3.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0)], via Wikimedia Commons\n\n\nInscreva-se:\nhttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCYEwurufany-SrB3vvnVLJA?sub_confirmation=1', '2018-01-24 11:14:20', 'idade da terra, datação absoluta, quantos anos tem a terra, quantos anos a terra tem, quantos anos tem o planeta terra, qual é a idade do planeta terra, o mundo tem quantos anos, quantos anos existe a terra, a verdadeira idade da terra, terra idade e evolução, a quanto tempo surgiu a terra, idade do mundo, qual a idade do mundo, A Meia Vida do Urânio 238, zircão, zircônio, geocronologia, geocronologia unb, geocronologia pdf, geofísico lunático, carbono 14', 'pt', 'pt', 'Geofsico Luntico', 'UCYEwurufany-SrB3vvnVLJA', 304, 814, 21, 1, 9, 0, 0, '2020-07-28 10:38:54'),
(196, 'ZIdeq3Jn8mY', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1111/ele.12224', '10.1111/ele.12224', 'X Eugen Warming - Polinizadores e Servios Ambientais: Dr. Mauricio Quesada', 'Faa Agora seu Cadastro para Receber Contedos Gratuitos sobre Biologia da Conservao: http://biologiadaconservacao.com.br/cadastre-se/\n\nDr. Mauricio Quesada, da Universidad Nacional Autnoma de Mxico (UNAM - Morelia), fala sobre sndromes de polinizao, biologia floral, e a importncia dos polinizadores primrios e secundrios para os servios ambientais...\n\nEle cita algumas das grandes questes de Darwin a respeito das Angiospermas, como a grande diversidade de morfologia floral, e a rpida evoluo desse grupo... o que ela chamava o "mistrio abominvel das flores"...\n\nO Dr. Quesada foi um dos palestrantes do X Eugen Warming Lectures in Evolutionary Ecology - Ecosystem Services in the Tropics: Now and Beyond, 2 a 4 de dezembro de 2014 - UFMG, Belo Horizonte, Brasil\n\n\nSite do Dr. Mauricio Quesada: http://www.oikos.unam.mx/prueba_menus/Mquesada/\n\n\nReferncia recomendada: http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/ele.12224/abstract;jsessionid=E7111D1BCAA811D371651D9FDFA4CCF4.f04t01', '2015-01-21 10:58:28', 'bcneea, Mauricio Quesada, Lucas Perillo, Bocaina, Bocaina Biologia da Concervação, Conservation Biology (Field Of Study), Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México, National Autonomous University Of Mexico (College/University), Pollinator (Literature Subject), Flowering Plant (Organism Classification), Eugenius Warming (Academic), Pollination Syndromes, Ecosystem Services', NULL, NULL, 'Bocaina Biologia da Conservao', 'UCLHfzHOMwCgV-_bvcp1sZUQ', 716, 434, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-28 10:38:54'),
