wrinkles, reactive oxygen species, algae', 'en', 'en', 'SciShow', 'UCZYTClx2T1of7BRZ86-8fow', 1087, 92400, 3005, 133, 285, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(237, 'lhC8ViPGoqU', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1088/0067-0049/212/2/18', '10.1088/0067-0049/212/2/18', '"An Atlas of Galaxy Spectra" - Michael Brown, et al', '"An Atlas of Galaxy Spectral Energy Distributions from the Ultraviolet to the Mid-infrared"\nhttp://dx.doi.org/10.1088/0067-0049/212/2/18', '2014-06-11 23:41:55', '+ Monash University + Astronomy + Galaxies + Spectra + Spitzer Space Telescope + SDSS, + galaxy +monash physics', NULL, NULL, 'MonashPhysicsAndAstronomy', 'UCC-6B62Wnzn0-huxwfhexDw', 259, 212, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(238, '_JMWb0OIEqQ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004393', '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004393, journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004393', 'Somalis and Ethiopians are mixed', 'There\'s been a lot of misleading back and forth on the internet about whether or not various populations of the Horn of Africa like Somalis, Habeshas, Oromos, Afars, Agaws and such are in fact "mixed" / whether or not these groups carry ancestry related to "Arabs" and other such groups and I was growing so tired of seeing weird or trollish videos like this one- :\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bu4OzKKlU9o\n\n-that I figured I\'d just release one of my own that shares as much factual information on this matter as possible.\n\nLink explaining autosomal DNA: http://www.isogg.org/wiki/Autosomal_DNA\n\nLink explaining why he "Afar" samples are in fact not Afars but Xamir/Xamtanga speaking Agaws:\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2014/12/afar-samples-from-autosomal-dna-studies.html\n\nLink explaining ADMIXTURE analyses: http://www.isogg.org/wiki/Admixture_analyses\n\nLink explaining a bit about South Cushites and their genetic impact on Southeast Africa:\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/05/south-cushitic-admixture-in-southeast.html\n\nLink to a blog post with citations explaining how we\'re learning from sampling ancient remains across Europe and other parts of Eurasia: http://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/06/population-genomics-of-bronze-age.html\n\n\nPeer reviewed studies referenced:\n\nTable at the beginning: http://arxiv.org/abs/1307.8014\n\nSecond table with various methods showcased: http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v517/n7534/full/nature13997.html\n\nFirst PCA: http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004393\n\nmtDNA results:  http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00414-012-0694-6\n\n\n"Ethio-Somali" showing ADMIXTURE analysis: http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004393\n\n\nMy blog posts on Horn African genetics for greater detail:\n\nHighly recommended post that goes into more detail when it comes to how these populations are "mixed": http://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/07/horn-africans-mixture-between-east.html\n\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2014/12/ethio-somali-is-farce.html\n\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/03/the-oromo-people-heterogeneous.html\n\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/04/the-jewishness-of-ethiopian-jews_7.html\n\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/01/the-omotic-cluster-horn-specific-cluster.html\n\nhttp://anthromadness.blogspot.ae/2015/06/sudanese-arabs-beni-ameri-beja-and.html\n\nEach blog post is sourced to the brim with peer-reviewed studies or other credible sources so nothing on there is just idle speculation but me basically just simplifying the data in various studies to aid in giving various readers some understanding about the genetic nature of various Horn Africans such as Somalis or Habeshas.\n\n-------\n\nI chose the title "Somalis and Ethiopians are mixed" over "Horn Africans are mixed" mostly because people are more likely to google as well as search for the former on Youtube in my humble opinion.\n\nEnjoy...', '2015-09-01 12:01:41', 'Horn Of Africa (Location), East Africa (Region), Somalia (Country), Ethiopia (Country), Eritrea (Country), Djibouti (Country), Somali People (Ethnicity), Amhara People (Ethnicity), Tigray-Tigrinya People (Ethnicity), Oromo People (Ethnicity), Afar People (Ethnicity), Agaw People (Ethnicity), Beta Israel (Ethnicity)', NULL, 'en', 'Awale', 'UCYkMB1vuZLCAEEtBJliCpxQ', 673, 37354, 258, 170, 395, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(239, '6GGtXN33jBM', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004401', '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004401, journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004401', 'A Follow Up To Irish and Northwestern European DNA comes from the middle east', 'I have found more sources to present....\n\nhttps://dnaconsultants.com/product/primeval-dna-test/ancient-israelites/\n\nhttps://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004401\n\nhttps://www.hope-of-israel.org/DNAofjews.html', '2019-06-16 09:40:30', '#hangoutsonair, Hangouts On Air, #hoa', NULL, NULL, 'Jewtube Hates Midnighthood\'s Channel', 'UCE1u8hsiMTdI27tuMF4lMAQ', 441, 196, 12, 1, 3, 0, 1, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(240, '4XPhOl_V5Bk', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004426', '10.1371/journal.pgen.1004426, journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004426', 'Kenapa Sebaiknya Tidak Konsumsi Suplemen Antioksidan Saat Puasa? Ini Alasannya', 'Halo Sobat Sehat,\n\nUntuk menjaga kesehatan selama sebulan berpuasa banyak orang yang mengandalkan suplemen antioksidan seperti vitamin C dan E.\nPadahal bila kita menerapkan pola makan seimbang, cukup sayur dan buah saat sahur maupun berbuka, semua kebutuhan nutrisi kita akan tercukupi.\n\nTahukah sobat bila konsumsi suplemen antioksidan saat berpuasa justru merugikan?\n\nSaat puasa gen anti-penuaan (sirtuin) ikut meningkat dan efeknya bikin kita awet muda. Kandungan antioksidan yang telalu tinggi pada suplemen akan menghambat aktivasi gen anti-penuaan ini.\n\nBagaimana mekanismenya? Yuk simak tuntas penjelasannya di video berikut\n\n\nReferensi:\n---------------------\nhttp://www.researchgate.net/profile/Stephen_Anton/publication/270220875_Practicality_of_Intermittent_Fasting_in_Humans_and_its_Effect_on_Oxidative_Stress_and_Genes_Related_to_Aging_and_Metabolism/links/54eb5df80cf2082851bdb3a9.pdf\nhttp://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3764375/\nhttp://www.impactaging.com/papers/v5/n3/full/100544.html\nhttps://www.researchgate.net/publication/338176367_Effects_of_Intermittent_Fasting_on_Health_Aging_and_Disease\nhttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/30197301\nhttps://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/article?id=10.1371/journal.pgen.1004426\n\nDisclaimer :\n----------------------\nWalaupun didasarkan pada bukti penelitian ilmiah yang sudah terpublikasi, semua yang disampaikan divideo ini hanya bersifat informasi dan tidak boleh menggantikan nasehat dari tenaga kesehatan profesional, konsultasikan kebutuhan kesehatan anda dengan tenaga kesehatan profesional seacara langsung.\nSantai sehat tidak bertanggung-jawab atas akibat karena penggunaan informasi yang ada di video tersebut.\n\nApakah sobat sehat punya topik yang ingin dibahas?\nSilakan komen dibawah ya\n\n#puasabikinawetmuda #awetmudadenganpuasa #puasatidakbutuhsuplemen', '2020-05-07 07:34:43', 'puasa bikin awet muda, Puasa tidak butuh suplemen, Tidak Konsumsi Suplemen Antioksidan Saat Puasa', NULL, 'id', 'Santai Sehat', 'UCK_lXdZtPYa4gRPzhs18mHw', 250, 476, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(241, 'JHgtCqriMY4', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1002/2013RG000448', '10.1002/2013RG000448', 'From primary school to PhD', 'Now this is a story all about how my life got flipped turned upside down, I\'d like to take a minute, just sit right there. This is how I got my PhD.\n\nIf I were to sum this whole video up in a quote, it would have to be "Never give up! Never surrender!" \n(By Grabthar\'s hammer, what a story Mark.)\nBut more seriously, this is one that I\'ve been meaning to make for a long time. Not least because I needed to sit my viva to do so! But also this video captures the underlying philosophy behind much of what I do. I\'m not the smartest person in the world, and I\'m certainly not the most talented at science or maths. But while you can never always be the smartest person in a room, you can always make yourself the hardest working one. Perspiration beats inspiration, and my refusal to quit has got me to where I am now.\n\n- All my PhD vlogs: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLiZiIJMDh4ymg8vXr5au4-vjuewqy1TI4\n- What I\'m doing next: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MHvv4_UgXuM\n\n- Atmospheric physics textbook (Wallace and Hobbs): http://bit.ly/introtoatmos\n- Never Split The Difference (Chris Voss): http://bit.ly/simonhaggle\n- Draw My Life video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W1KphCUrqJQ\n- Brewer-Dobson circulation: http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/2013RG000448/full\n- My headphones: http://bit.ly/runningbluetoothheadphones\n\nYou can support the channel by donating at http://www.patreon.com/simonoxfphys\n\n---------- II ----------\n\nMusic by:\n- Pacific Coast Strings (https://soundcloud.com/pacific-coast-strings/coldplay-viva-la-vida)\n- Adam Radford (https://soundcloud.com/adam-radford/viva-la-vida-cover)\n\nFilmed on my Canon 80D http://bit.ly/simonvlog80D (and 5D mk II)\nEditing done in Premiere. \n\nHuge thanks to my supporters on Patreon: Dan Hanvey, David Efird, Michael Phillips, Neudys Almonte, Fraser Birks, Martin Hermes, Anh Duong Phan, Luca Schumann, Katy P, Rhys Rickard-Frost, Cameron Matchett, Lachlan Woods, Tim Boxall, Simon Vaes, Gabriele Mozzicato, Jawad Alalasi, Gaia Frazao Nery, Kodzo, Josh Ruby, Claire Anthony, Eve Dillon, Rowan Gow, Matthias Loos, James Bridges, James Craig, Angela, Sanaa Al Derei, Mark Anthony Magro, Liam, Theresa Wang, Kieran Kelly, Wendover Productions, Kendra Johnson, Caitlin Louise, and Real Engineering (nice hair Brian).\n\n---------- II ----------\n\nI am Simon, a fourth year PhD candidate at the University of Exeter. I upload videos on bits of science which are relevant to what I do, and sometimes just because they\'re really cool.\n\nVlogs from Oxford students - http://www.youtube.com/oxvlog\nMy twitter - http://www.twitter.com/simonoxfphys\nMy facebook - http://www.facebook.com/youtubesimon\nMy insta - http://www.instagram.com/simonoxfphys\nMy goodreads - http://www.goodreads.com/simonoxfphys\n\nThanks to Vlogbrothers for their sponsorship of this video. Money from the Foundation to Decrease Worldsuck contributed to equipment used in this video.', '2018-02-12 12:30:01', 'University of Exeter, vlog, uni, university, college, PhD, grad school, University of Oxford, school, maths, GCSE, failure, redemption, motivation, inspiration, never give up, study, studying, PhD viva, viva, viva voce, story, from primary school to phd, simon clark, simon oxford physics', 'en-GB', 'en-US', 'Simon Clark', 'UCRRr_xrOm66qaigIbwFLvbQ', 1283, 281057, 12307, 112, 925, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
(242, 'z9YZPVBzVas', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '10.1111/gcb.12502', '10.1111/gcb.12502', 'Humboldt Squid facts: some might say "jumbo" | Animal Fact Files', 'The Humboldt squid is also known as the red devil squid and the jumbo flying squid. These cephalopods don\'t quite reach the gargantuan sizes of giant and colossal squid, but they can still pack a punch with their fist sized beaks. Humboldt squid live along the Pacific coasts of the Americas partaking in nightly migrations to the water\'s surface for midnight meals. These giant squid are believed to communicate with one another in the dark waters of the ocean by flashing in multiple patterns of light.\n\nScientific Name: Dosidicus gigas\nRange: eastern Pacific ocean\nSize: up to 100lbs (45kg); 8ft (2.4m)\nDiet: fish, crustaceans, other cephalopods\nLifespan: 2 years or fewer\n\nYou can learn more on:\nTwitter - https://twitter.com/animalfactfiles\nFacebook - https://facebook.com/animalfactfiles\n\n---\n\nWe always do what we can to be as accurate as possible, but we\'re only human; if you catch a mistake please let us know and provide a link for verification!\n\n---\n\nAll images, videos and sound effects used herein are 1) public domain, 2) used under a Creative Commons license, 3) used with the express permission of the copyright holder, or 4) used under the parameters of Fair Use law.\n\nCredits via Youtube:\nAlan Lundell - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yGHtS8E77z4\nThe Company of Biologists - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=chYn-LxCAFQ\n\nCredits via Wiki Users:\nBristow, Laura A.; Mohr, Wiebke; Ahmerkamp, Soeren; Kuypers, Marvel M.M. - https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Nitrogen_cycle_OMZ.jpg\nChris huh - https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Oceanic_divisions.svg\nCaptmondo - https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:SquidEggCases-MontereryAquarium-April2-07.png\nThroast - https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Colossalsquid.png\n\nOther attributions:\nEcologia Azul - https://vimeo.com/129937893\nDiver Jackie - https://vimeo.com/33386061; https://vimeo.com/31889277; https://vimeo.com/33471733; https://vimeo.com/33471542\nMatt Davidson - https://vimeo.com/225629421\nJ J King 2 - https://vimeo.com/97042360\n\n\nWebsites used for research collection:\nhttps://www.google.com/books/edition/The_Biogeography_and_Numerical_Taxonomy/qYVQ4b446LUC\nhttps://www.google.com/books/edition/Octopus/m-Mv7awvtIQC\nhttps://www.google.com/books/edition/Mercury_in_the_Environment/MSVKDr-Y-VYC?\nhttps://www.google.com/books/edition/Giant_Squid/CPGD2kCze4MC\nhttps://www.google.com/books/edition/American_Monsters/RZOpAQAAQBAJ\nhttps://www.pices.int/publications/pices_press/Volume13/July_2005/pp_30_31_squid.pdf\nhttps://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0079661110000388\nhttps://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/journal-of-the-marine-biological-association-of-the-united-kingdom/article/natural-egg-mass-deposition-by-the-humboldt-squid-dosidicus-gigas-in-the-gulf-of-california-and-characteristics-of-hatchlings-and-paralarvae/581EC029C37E67A49C4C46976EE5492F\nhttps://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00343-013-2036-z\nhttps://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.1111/gcb.12502?casa_token=nzVWhtzgNHsAAAAA%3AhFdRlC6feFF8BRMjOcNMO22tKSuRJow26XX3AF6EQ-GkICxzgN8oORvvhC8hYWyZl6CCvN4mRaX06Jx9\nhttps://www.researchgate.net/publication/258332427_Dosidicus_gigas_Humboldt_squid\nhttps://tinyurl.com/yc66jqrg\nhttps://animaldiversity.org/accounts/Dosidicus_gigas\nhttps://www.mbari.org/humboldt-squid-signaling\nhttps://ocean.si.edu/ocean-life/invertebrates/humboldt-squid-shoots-ink\nhttps://comicvine.gamespot.com/forums/off-topic-5/impurest-s-guide-to-animals-39-humboldt-squid-1618337\nhttps://www.telegraph.co.uk/tv/2017/11/05/blue-planet-iis-humboldt-squid-cannibalistic-deep-sea-horror/#:~:text=But%20the%20nightmarish%20scene%20only,body%20weight%20daily%20to%20survive.\n\n\nThis video is licensed under a CC BY-SA 3.0 license (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/)*.\n\n*you can find information about all the different types of CC licenses here: https://creativecommons.org/\n**changes were made to the original', '2020-07-24 19:00:11', 'humboldt, humboldt squid, humboldt squid facts, humboldt squid animal facts, humboldt squid documentary, humboldt squid animal fact files, red devil squid, red devil squid facts, red devil squid video, humboldt squid video, jumbo squid, jumbo squid facts, jumbo squid fact video, jumbo squid animal facts, jumbo flying squid, squid facts, squid animal facts, squid fact video, squid animal fact files, squid information, squid documentary, animal facts, animal learning, facts', NULL, 'en', 'Animal Fact Files', 'UCJ6OEgocfxp6kpNAn04oTZA', 224, 373, 45, 0, 15, 0, 0, '2020-07-31 18:37:18'),
